-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-archive1x.png?w=18 18w, https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-archive1x.png?w=36 36w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 18px) 85vw, 18px\" data-attachment-id=\"7077\" data-permalink=\"https://themeshaper.com/2018/06/04/designing-a-gutenberg-powered-theme-music/blog-archive1x/\" data-orig-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-archive1x.png\" data-orig-size=\"375,3089\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Blog-Archive@1x\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-archive1x.png?w=36\" data-large-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-archive1x.png?w=124\" /></a>\n<a href=\'https://themeshaper.com/2018/06/04/designing-a-gutenberg-powered-theme-music/blog-post2x/\'><img width=\"50\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post2x.png?w=50\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post2x.png?w=50 50w, https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post2x.png?w=100 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 50px) 85vw, 50px\" data-attachment-id=\"7075\" data-permalink=\"https://themeshaper.com/2018/06/04/designing-a-gutenberg-powered-theme-music/blog-post2x/\" data-orig-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post2x.png\" data-orig-size=\"2040,6178\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Blog-Post@2x\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post2x.png?w=99\" data-large-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post2x.png?w=338\" /></a>\n<a href=\'https://themeshaper.com/2018/06/04/designing-a-gutenberg-powered-theme-music/blog-post1x/\'><img width=\"18\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post1x.png?w=18\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post1x.png?w=18 18w, https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post1x.png?w=36 36w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 18px) 85vw, 18px\" data-attachment-id=\"7079\" data-permalink=\"https://themeshaper.com/2018/06/04/designing-a-gutenberg-powered-theme-music/blog-post1x/\" data-orig-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post1x.png\" data-orig-size=\"375,3089\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Blog-Post@1x\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post1x.png?w=36\" data-large-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/blog-post1x.png?w=124\" /></a>\n</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Backing up and thinking about page design helped me shift focus to other, more traditional components that needed to be designed too: archive pages, page footers, post headers, etc. Designing these wasn’t all that different than it would’ve been without Gutenberg. In a way, we’ve all been designing with blocks all along — we just hadn’t called them blocks. Take a look at this entry summary: </span></p>\n<p><img data-attachment-id=\"7084\" data-permalink=\"https://themeshaper.com/2018/06/04/designing-a-gutenberg-powered-theme-music/entry-summary/\" data-orig-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/entry-summary.png\" data-orig-size=\"3212,2012\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Entry-Summary\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/entry-summary.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/entry-summary.png?w=840\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-7084\" src=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/entry-summary.png\" alt=\"Entry-Summary.png\" width=\"3212\" height=\"2012\" srcset=\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/entry-summary.png 3212w, https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/entry-summary.png?w=150&amp;h=94 150w, https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/entry-summary.png?w=300&amp;h=188 300w, https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/entry-summary.png?w=768&amp;h=481 768w, https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/entry-summary.png?w=1024&amp;h=641 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px\" /></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">If I’d designed this theme pre-Gutenberg, I still would’ve designed each one of those pieces — they’re all fairly standard parts of a theme. But thanks to Gutenberg, each piece is part of a clear pattern library, to be reused throughout the design by me </span><i><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">and</span></i><span style=\"font-weight:400;\"> by the user. That&#8217;s pretty cool. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">I’d gone into this project thinking I’d spend most of my time styling individual blocks, but I ended up splitting my time pretty evenly between designing block variations and overall page elements. In that sense, this wasn’t as drastically different from a traditional theme design as I’d anticipated. </span></p>\n<h2>Prototypes</h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">I’d been getting ongoing feedback from Allan throughout the process above, but once we were happy with the page designs above, we gathered  with the rest of the Theme team to get broader design feedback. </span><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">To help with that process, I pulled all my comps together into a prototype. This took just a few minutes to do, and really helped others get a sense of how the theme will work in practice. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">I created two separate prototypes with Invision: </span><a href=\"https://automattic.invisionapp.com/share/HZGCYKAPA6S#/screens/286254235_Homepage%C2%A0\"><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">one for desktop</span></a><span style=\"font-weight:400;\"> and </span><a href=\"https://automattic.invisionapp.com/share/RFGFS8NHS73#/screens/286260159_Homepage\"><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">one for mobile</span></a><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">. </span><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">If my transition from block design to full-page design was about looking at the bigger picture, these prototypes stepped back still further: they showed us the context <em>around</em> that big picture. We were all able to see the designs on-device and test some basic interactions. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">The team’s feedback was (as usual) very helpful — we made some subtle revisions to text contrast, adjusted a number of margins, and kicked off a lot of iteration on the mobile menu treatment. </span></p>\n<h2>Development</h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Allan had been focused on the build from the beginning, and had the majority of the framework in place at this point. After our design feedback session, I jumped into the code too.  </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">From the development angle, we’d already determined a few things in the design that we couldn’t do, or that would take too much effort. For instance, in my initial design comp I’d had a series of backgrounds run down the page. Gutenberg doesn’t have a method for doing something like that today; despite my wishful design thinking, there’s no method for layering a background behind a group of blocks. We could’ve accomplished it through customizer settings, but we shelved the idea in favor of keeping things simple. We also abandoned a bunch of the play buttons I&#8217;d originally included, since those&#8217;ll require some custom blocks (more on that later). </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Once I jumped into the code, my main revelation was that there were </span><i><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">way</span></i><span style=\"font-weight:400;\"> more block options than I’d originally anticipated. A number of blocks had options I’d never noticed before. I hadn’t realized that paragraph blocks could be set to full width, or that cover image blocks could be floated left or right. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">In addition, I realized some design decisions I’d made were actually supposed to be user-editable: I’d overlooked the fact that users can edit the text alignment and image opacity for the cover image block. This required more design exploration, but it guided us towards a much more customizable theme — definitely a win in the end.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Beyond those updates, the majority of the design-oriented development work involved minor fixes and adjustments — polishing up the CSS to make sure it aligned with the intent of the original design. </span></p>\n<h2>Next steps</h2>\n<p>Now that we’ve had our initial release, Allan and I plan to build a separate plugin with complementary music-centric blocks, like a tour dates block and a mashup of a cover image and an audio player. We’ll hope to showcase those at some point in the future.</p>\n<p>In the meantime, keep an eye out for the next post in the series: Allan’s experience from a development perspective.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"https://themeshaper.com/2018/06/04/designing-a-gutenberg-powered-theme-music/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:29:\"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/\";a:2:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:3:\"url\";s:82:\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/gutenberg-music-theme-mockup-2.jpg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"content\";a:16:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"\n			\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:2:{s:3:\"url\";s:82:\"https://themeshaper.files.wordpress.com